## Conclusion

This project demonstrates the development of an intelligent line-following robot with obstacle-avoidance capabilities using Arduino and the L298N motor driver. 
By integrating IR sensors for line detection and an ultrasonic sensor for obstacle sensing, the robot can autonomously follow a predefined path while safely navigating around obstacles.

The project provided valuable experience in embedded systems, sensor interfacing, motor control, robotics, and Arduino programming. It serves as a practical example of autonomous robotic navigation and can be further enhanced with advanced path-planning and control algorithms.
